FBIS4-43906 "drweu121__a94025" FBIS-WEU-94-121-A Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 ANNEX Germany SPD Holds Extraordinary Congress in Halle 22 Jun SPD Holds Extraordinary Congress in Halle 22 Jun Scharping Named Official Candidate AU2206153094 Hamburg DPA in German 1416 GMT 22 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2206153094 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] Halle (DPA) -- Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD] Chairman Rudolf Scharping is the official SPD candidate for the chancellor's office. At the special congress in Halle, 479 of 502 -- that is, an approval of 93 percent -- delegates voted for him on Wednesday afternoon [22 June]. The 46-year-old minister president of Rhineland-Palatinate did not have an opponent in the secret vote.
